President Obama has issued a statement expressing his gratitude to Mary Schapiro, the Chairman of the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), for her leadership and hard work during her time in office. Schapiro will be leaving her post next month, and the President has announced that he intends to designate Elisse Walter, a current Commissioner, as Chair upon Schapiro's departure. The President is confident that Walter's experience will serve her well in her new position and is grateful that she has agreed to help lead the agency.